# Harmony AI App Tech Context
@Core: React Native 0.83.1, TypeScript, React Navigation (Native Stack), React Native Paper (MD3).
@State: React Hooks (current), Context API (theme/auth/emoji), Redux/Zustand (future complex state).
@Data: SQLite (messages/characters/interactions/emoji_actions, future), AsyncStorage (settings/preferences/reply mode), SQLCipher encryption, React Native Keychain (secure storage).
@Network: Axios (REST), WebSocket (real-time), reconnection logic, retry with backoff, session resume on reconnect.
@Build: Metro Bundler, Gradle 8.13 (NOT 9.0+), Android SDK API 24-33, JDK 17.
@Dev Tools: TypeScript compiler, ESLint, Prettier, Jest, React Native Debugger, hot reload.
@Future Integrations:
- On-Device AI: React Native Executorch (PyTorch models, quantized up to 7B)
- Audio: React Native Voice (STT), React Native TTS
- Media: Image Picker, Camera, FFmpeg
- Services: FCM (push), biometric auth, cloud backup
@APIs: Harmony Link REST (characters, config, messages, sync) + WebSocket (real-time messages, status, typing, emoji actions, interactions).
@Performance: Lazy loading, image optimization, FlatList virtualization, memoization, code splitting, JOIN-based queries for chat list previews.
@Security: EncryptedStorage, HTTPS, token auth, SSL pinning (consideration), no plaintext credentials.
@Platforms: Android 7.0+ (API 24), target API 33.
@Workflow: Local dev with Metro → emulator/ADB testing → release builds → Play Store (future).
@Key Deps: react 19.2.0, react-native 0.83.1, @react-navigation/*  ^7.x, react-native-paper ^5.x, @react-native-async-storage/async-storage ^2.x, react-native-sqlite-storage ^6.x, eventemitter3 ^5.x, uuid ^10.x, music-metadata v11, react-native-device-info.
@ModularConfig:
- App mirrors Harmony Link frontend's schema-driven provider configuration approach
- providerFieldSchemas.ts: 15 provider schemas (openai, openaicompatible, openrouter, elevenlabs, kindroid, kajiwoto, characterai, harmonyspeech_stt/vad/tts, comfyui, tts_openai, rag_*, stt_openai/vad_openai, google, xai, anthropic). No module-specific schemas — one schema per provider, module-specific fields merged into main schemas with tooltips.
- moduleConfiguration.ts: module type definitions, provider options per module (movement includes Google/xAI/Anthropic), MODULES/PROVIDERS constants
- moduleDefaults.ts: PROVIDER_DEFAULTS and MODULE_DEFAULTS for form initialization (Google/xAI/Anthropic defaults: maxtokens 200)
- configHelpers.ts: utility functions for provider field resolution
- Inline provider config editing in ModuleConfigEditScreen (provider type chips + form fields)
- Advanced Sampling Parameters component for OpenAI-family extended params
- Dual-slot support: standard modules (single "provider" slot), STT (dual "transcription"/"vad" slots)
- Model field unification: migration 000030, single `model` column per provider config table
- Shared isProviderConfigInUse() helper with UNION ALL for existence checks
@Phase09-LifecycleUI:
- Harmony Link management UI adds Lifecycle Settings tab to character profile
- Exposes lifecycle_config fields for per-entity autonomy configuration
- Not directly synced to app (app receives emotion state via sync, not lifecycle config)
- App's autonomy behavior controlled locally, not via Harmony Link lifecycle settings
@Interactions:
- DB: interactions table with entity_id, interaction_scope, participant_key, participant_ids, status, presence_type, summary, memory_id, continued_interaction_id
- Migrations 24-28 sequentially applied: create_interactions, drop_session_id, add_summary, memory_lifecycle_fields, add_presence_type
- Repository: interactions.ts with CRUD, participant key derivation, scope derivation, JOIN-based chat list queries
- Participant key derivation: sorted entity ID pair join for private, sorted full set join for group, empty string for world
- Chat list query pattern: JOIN conversation_messages + interactions for single-round-trip last message preview, two-phase TEXT column loading for large audio/image data
@Emoji:
- Emoji Sets: native (platform default), twemoji (Twitter 64px sprite), noto (Google 64px sprite) — bundled as PNG spritesheets in src/assets/emoji/sheets/
- Emoji Data: Pre-built category-organized data (src/services/EmojiService.ts), keyword-based search, skin tone variants (5 modifiers)
- DB: emoji_actions table (migrations 22-23) with per-entity emoji → action mappings, emotion_effects JSON column, cooldown_seconds, soft delete via deleted_at
- Emotion model: Ekman8 base emotions (joy, sadness, trust, disgust, fear, anger, surprise, anticipation) with signed delta intensity (-5.0 to +5.0)
- AdditionalEffects payload: { emotionEffects: EmotionEffect[] } — packaged per SEND_MESSAGE via EmojiService.resolveMessageActions()
- EmojiAwareText: Segments text into emoji/text spans using regex; EmojiText renders with sprite caching
- Context: EmojiContext (style preferences, set selection, skin tone), EmojiProvider wraps app root
